        <abstract> 
<p>Has been working hard on <hi rend="italic">Mimosa albida</hi>. Could JDH ever make its opposite leaflets shut up close, as in sleep, when he irritated them? CD doubts they do, except in sleep. Thinks movement a protection against water.</p>  
<p>Has examined only one specimen of <hi rend="italic">Eucalyptus</hi>.</p>  
<p>Cannot believe JDH’s results from cutting a hole in pitcher in his <hi rend="italic">Nepenthes</hi> experiment.</p> 
        </abstract>
